'''Academicians''' are distinguished members of the '''[[National Academy of Science and Technology]]'''[[National Academy of Science and Technology| ]](''abbreviated as'' '''NAST'''), the highest recognition and scientific advisory body of the [[Philippines]]. The first Academicians were appointed in 1978 by President [[Ferdinand E. Marcos]]. Possible members are distinguished scientists in their own field which are nominated by members of the scientific community. The current NAST members deliberate on the membership of an individual following strict rules and regulations. From their ranks, the next [[National Scientist of the Philippines]] would be nominated and approved by the [[President of the Philippines]]. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Year elected as Academician ! Name ! Field of specialization |- | rowspan=10|1978 | [[Paulo Campos|Paulo C. Campos]], M.D.<ref group="lower-alpha" name=":0">Deceased</ref><ref group="lower-alpha" name=":9">Later conferred the rank of a National Scientist in 1989</ref> | Nuclear Medicine |- | [[Alfredo Lagmay|Alfredo V. Lagmay]], Ph.D.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /><ref group="lower-alpha" name=":8">Later conferred the rank of a National Scientist in 1988</ref> | Experimental Psychology |- | Cecilio F. Lopez, Dr. Phil.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /> | Philippine Linguistics and Oriental Studies |- | Tito A. Mijares, Ph.D.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /> | Statistics |- | [[Juan Salcedo, Jr.|Juan S. Salcedo, Jr]]., M.D., D.Sc.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /><ref group="lower-alpha" name=":2">Later conferred the rank of a National Scientist in 1978</ref> | Nutrition and Public Health |- | Alfredo C. Santos, Dr. Phil.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /><ref name=":2" group="lower-alpha" /> | Physical Chemistry |- | Dioscoro L. Umali, Ph.D.<ref name=":0" group="lower-alpha" /><ref name=":22" group="lower-alpha">Later conferred the rank of a National Scientist in 1986</ref> | Genetics and Plant Breeding |