The '''Zhongman Petroleum and Natural Gas Group''' (or '''ZPEC''') is a Chinese oilfield services company.
==History== The company was founded in 2003.<ref name="yicai">{{cite news|title=ZPNG Wins USD23 Million Gas Drilling Project in Pakistan|url=https://www.yicaiglobal.com/news/zpng-wins-usd23-million-gas-drilling-project-pakistan|work=Yicai Global|date=April 9, 2018}}</ref> The company received backing from [[Sequoia Capital]].<ref name="sequoia">{{cite web|title=Companies|url=https://www.sequoiacap.com/companies/zhongman|publisher=Sequoia Capital}}</ref>
Reuters in December 2017 reported the company was in talks with [[Gazprom Neft]] to take a stake in the Chonsk oil fields development project in [[Siberia]].<ref name="reuters">{{cite news|title=Gazprom Neft in talks with China's ZPEC over east Siberian oil fields project - sources|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-russia-china-oil/gazprom-neft-in-talks-with-chinas-zpec-over-east-siberian-oil-fields-project-sources-idUSKBN1ED1VN|agency=Reuters|date=December 19, 2017}}</ref>
==Projects== *{{flag|Iraq}} - Awarded by Iraqi government a $526.6 million drilling deal for drilling of 66 production oil wells at the West Qurna Two oilfield<ref name="reuters2">{{cite news|title=Iraq approves $526 mln drilling deal for West Qurna oilfield|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/iraq-energy-west-qurna/iraq-approves-526-mln-drilling-deal-for-west-qurna-oilfield-idUSL5N0YA4RN20150519|work=Reuters|date=May 20, 2015}}</ref> *{{flag|Pakistan}} - Awarded by Pakistan Petroleum a US$23 million drilling project in Pakistan in 2018.<ref name="yicai"/>
